Module-2 Transformer
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
To understand the transformer archecture , we must understand the RNN, LSTM:

Transformer:- A Transformer is a deep learning architecture introduced in 2017 
that uses Self-Attention to process data in parallel instead of sequentially like RNNs and LSTMs.

Why Transformer needed:-
RNN (Recurrent neural network):-
-> Squential processing.
-> Slow training.
-> Poor-Long-range memory.
-> vanishing gradients.

eg:-" The cat, which was sitting on the sofa for many hours , suddenly jumped."
-> The AI may forgot that who jumpped from sofa.

LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory):-
->LSTM improved memory using gates.
Advantages:- Better long-term memory.
Problems:- 
->Still Sequential.
->Difficult to parallellise.
->slow for large datasets.

Transformer architure:
It revolutionized Natural Language Processing (NLP) by replacing RNNs and 
LSTMs with an Attention Mechanism that processes all words simultaneously.

Applications:-
->ChatGPT
->Microsoft Copilot
->GPT Models


Word1 ↔ Word2 ↔ Word3 ↔ Word4

Benefits:-
->Parallel processing
->Faster training
->Better context understanding
->Long-range dependency learning.


